			"type": "RESPONSE",
			"payload": "That's a profound philosophical question with different answers depending on your perspective:\n\n**Philosophical views:**\n- **Existentialism**: We create our own meaning and purpose\n- **Religious perspectives**: To fulfill a divine purpose or spiritual growth\n- **Secular humanism**: To improve wellbeing, reduce suffering, and help others\n\n**Biological view:**\n- From an evolutionary standpoint, life exists to survive and reproduce\n\n**Practical perspective:**\n- Many find meaning through relationships, work, learning, creativity, or helping others\n\nIf you meant something more specific—like why humans evolved, why we exist individually, or the purpose of life—I'm happy to explore that further. What aspect interests you most?",
